name: Guo Guangchang
bio: Guo, a billionaire and one of China’s most celebrated entrepreneurs was reported missing on December 10, 2015. The following day Fosun International Ltd., a listed arm of the Fosun Group the company he founded and of which he is Chairman, released a statement that Guo was “currently assisting in certain investigations carried out by Mainland judiciary authorities.” On December 13, Caijing, a Chinese magazine, reported that Guo had returned home safely. And a report on the website of the People’s Daily cites the Shanghai Muncipal Discipline and Inspection Committee describing Guo as having been involved in an investigation that concluded on December 14, 2015. Earlier in 2015, Xinhua reported that Guo had granted favors to Wang Zongnan, the General Manager of the Shanghai Bright Food Group, but that he had not been accused of wrongdoing. Wang was sentenced to 18 years in prison for corruption in August of 2015.
